## Background and Motivation

Today, `ValidatablePropertyInfo` uses reflection to get the property value.

It should be more performant for the generated code to use access property getter directly, which is faster than reflection. This proposal allows `ValidatablePropertyInfo` to have an extensibility point for derived classes to control how to get the property value. In this case, the source-generated implementations will use just access the property.

## Proposed API

```diff
namespace Microsoft.Extensions.Validation;

public abstract class ValidatablePropertyInfo : IValidatablePropertyInfo
{
     // Default implementation uses reflection.
     // Derived classes can change that for performance.
+    protected virtual object? GetPropertyValue(object containingObject)
+        => Property.GetValue(containingObject);
}
```

## Usage Examples

```csharp
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;

public class MyValidatableInfo : ValidatablePropertyInfo
{
    public override object? GetPropertyValue(object containingObject)
        => ((ModelType)containingObject).PropName;
}
```

